X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE:https://events.iu.edu/live/image/gid/261/width/168/heig
 ht/168/crop/1/src_region/0\,0\,2154\,2154/30477_HarlequinSquare.rev.17733
 19690.jpg
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE-CAPTION:"Harlequin" is one of the eye-catching costume 
 designs in the Robert O'Hearn collection in the Indiana University Archiv
 es. Though the production and performance dates are unknown\, the distinc
 t design can be recognized as coming from <em>Arlecchino\,</em> a German 
 opera written by Ferruccio Busoni.
X-LIVEWHALE-ALL-DAY:1
X-LIVEWHALE-CONTACT-INFO:<div class="address--organization">\n  Indiana U
 niversity Archives\n</div>\n<div class="address--line-1">\n  1320 E. 10th
  Street Herman B Wells Library E460\n</div>\n<div class="address--localit
 y">\n  Bloomington\, IN 47401<br />\n  <a href="mailto:archives@iu.edu\;"
 >archives@iu.edu\;</a> (812)855-1127\n</div>
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>This new exhibition features a variety of costume 
 and scenic designs by the late Robert O'Hearn\, alumnus and professor eme
 ritus of opera studies in the Jacobs School of Music at Indiana Universit
 y. O'Hearn also worked as an opera\, ballet\, and theater designer for th
 e Metropolitan Opera\, IU Opera and Ballet Theater\, Broadway\, and other
  opera and theater companies across the country and Europe. A selection f
 rom the 600+ works that are now held by the University Archives celebrate
 s O'Hearn as a visual storyteller\, talented artist\, and impactful desig
 ner.</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-TAGS:Indiana University Archives|Theatre and Opera
X-LIVEWHALE-CUSTOM-ROOM-NUMBER:E460
X-LIVEWHALE-REPEATS-UNTIL:2026-06-26 13:00:00
