X-SOURCE:IU Bloomington Libraries
DTSTART:20260501T180000Z
DTEND:20260501T190000Z
LOCATION:Lilly Library (1200 E. Seventh St.) - Room Number: North Gallery
GEO:39.167909;-86.518974
SUMMARY:Guided tours of the Lilly Library
DESCRIPTION:You'll visit the Lilly's main galleries\, and your expert gui
 de will talk about some of the Lilly's highlights including the Gutenberg
  Bible\, John James Audubon's Birds of America\, and our current exhibiti
 ons from the Lilly Library collections. Additional hands-on time with rot
 ating selections from the collections will follow. These selections inclu
 de medieval manuscripts\, artists books\, and one of the John Ford's Best
  Director Oscars. Non-flash photography is permitted\, seating is availab
 le throughout the tour\, and the building is wheelchair accessible. The t
 our generally lasts a little less than one hour and is open to all.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  You'll visit the Lilly's main galleries
 \, and your expert guide will talk about some of the Lilly's highlights i
 ncluding the Gutenberg Bible\, John James Audubon's <em>Birds of America<
 /em>\, and our current exhibitions from the Lilly Library collections. Ad
 ditional hands-on time with rotating selections from the collections will
  follow. These selections include medieval manuscripts\, artists books\, 
 and one of the John Ford's Best Director Oscars. Non-flash photography is
  permitted\, seating is available throughout the tour\, and the building 
 is wheelchair accessible. The tour generally lasts a little less than one
  hour and is open to all.</p>
