BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU Bloomington Libraries
DTSTART:20260502T150000Z
DTEND:20260502T180000Z
LOCATION:WYLIE HOUSE (307 E. SECOND STREET)
GEO:39.161697;-86.5309
SUMMARY:Saturday Crafternoons at the Wylie House Museum
DESCRIPTION:The exhibition highlights Louisa Wylie Boisen\, eldest daught
 er of IU professor Theophilus Wylie\, and her accomplishments as a brave\
 , complex\, and cherished woman. Her horticultural impact can still be se
 en at the Wylie House today\, over 70 years later! Come to the Wylie Hous
 e Museum in May (on Saturdays\, May 2\, 23\, and 30 - closed on May 9 and
  16) and make your own mini WHM garden to cherish\, in memory of Louisa W
 ylie Boisen.  Saturday Crafternoons are a free event for families\, stude
 nts\, and friends of all ages! Activities change monthly. Check the Wylie
  House Museum socials and website (https://libraries.indiana.edu/wylie-ho
 use-museum) for updated information\, parking information\, and museum to
 ur hours.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The exhibition highlights Louisa Wylie 
 Boisen\, eldest daughter of IU professor Theophilus Wylie\, and her accom
 plishments as a brave\, complex\, and cherished woman. Her horticultural 
 impact can still be seen at the Wylie House today\, over 70 years later! 
 Come to the Wylie House Museum in May (on Saturdays\, May 2\, 23\, and 30
  - closed on May 9 and 16) and make your own mini WHM garden to cherish\,
  in memory of Louisa Wylie Boisen.</p><p>  Saturday Crafternoons are a fr
 ee event for families\, students\, and friends of all ages! Activities ch
 ange monthly. Check the Wylie House Museum socials and <a href="https://l
 ibraries.indiana.edu/wylie-house-museum">website</a> for updated informat
 ion\, parking information\, and museum tour hours.</p>
UID:20260502T150000Z-2276510@events.iu.edu
DTSTAMP:20260422T124954Z
URL:https://events.iu.edu/libraries/event/2276510-saturday-crafternoons-a
 t-the-wylie-house-museum
CATEGORIES:Community events
LAST-MODIFIED:20260422T165122Z
ATTACH:https://events.iu.edu/live/image/gid/261/width/168/height/168/crop
 /1/src_region/0,0,538,538/22599_Crafternoon_Image_002.rev.1723234996.jpg
X-LIVEWHALE-TYPE:events
X-LIVEWHALE-ID:2276510
X-LIVEWHALE-TIMEZONE:America/New_York
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE:https://events.iu.edu/live/image/gid/261/width/168/heig
 ht/168/crop/1/src_region/0\,0\,538\,538/22599_Crafternoon_Image_002.rev.1
 723234996.jpg
X-LIVEWHALE-COST:Free
X-LIVEWHALE-CONTACT-INFO:<p>\n  Melania Majowicz\, <a href="mailto:memajo
 @iu.edu">memajo@iu.edu</a>&#160\;\n</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>\n  Welcome to spring! The Wylie House Museum's ne
 west exhibition\, Louisa's Garden\, opens May 1!&#160\;\n</p>
